Fresh Pi session: TEST THE CHANGES THROUGH THE UI (agentic, round {{run.round}}).

Inputs:
- Manual-testing spec: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/spec.md
- Worktree-rooted test server (one-shot, current round): {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/test-server-{{run.round}}.json
- Worktree (repository root): {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Drive an agentic browser test of the worktree-rooted test server against the manual-testing spec. The test-server JSON artifact records the current round's host/port/pid/cwd/command/started_at/lifecycle — read that one (NOT an earlier round's) to avoid stale-server hazards.

Rules:
- Read the test-server artifact for the current round to get host/port.
- Exercise the surfaces listed in the spec; capture expected evidence.
- Verify responsive/console checks and acceptance criteria from the spec.
- Do not edit source code; testing only (you may read files and run non-mutating commands).
- Do not push or create pull requests.

Stale-server hazard:
- Each round starts a fresh server on a new OS-assigned port. Always use the port from test-server-{{run.round}}.json; an old artifact's port is stale.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/status-{{run.round}}.json
- If failing: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status JSON examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"all spec surfaces verified","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"console errors on /runs view","issues_file":"manual-testing/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}

If the spec declares manual testing may be skipped (with an explicit gate/rationale), validate the gate is met and write a passing status citing the skip rationale.